------------------------------
Installation and Configuration
------------------------------

Plasma
---------
Prerequisites: MKL blas

1. Find the packages at: http://icl.cs.utk.edu/plasma/software/index.html

2. > tar -xf plasma-installer_2.5.2.tar.gz
   > cd plasma-installer_2.5.2
   > ./setup.py --prefix="/path/to/plasma/installation"
                --cc="/usr/bin/gcc-4.7"
                --fc="/usr/bin/gfortran-4.7"
                --fflags="-O2 -fPIC -I/opt/intel/mkl/include -L/opt/intel/mkl/lib"
                --cflags="-O2 -fPIC -I/opt/intel/mkl/include -L/opt/intel/mkl/lib"
                --blaslib="-L/opt/intel/mkl/lib/intel64 -lmkl_intel_lp64 -lmkl_sequential -lmkl_core -lpthread
                          -L/opt/intel/lib/intel64 -limf"
                --downlapack
                --downcblas
                --downlapc
                --notesting
                --noopt="-O0 -fPIC"

3. Edit your .bashrc file (or .profile file) and add the following lines
replacing {PLASMA_INSTALL_DIR} by the correct pathname of your plasma installation

export PLASMA_ROOT={PLASMA_INSTALL_DIR}
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH="$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$PLASMA_ROOT/lib"

Hpx
----
Edit your .bashrc file (or .profile file) and add the following line
replacing {HPX_INSTALL_DIR} by the correct pathname of your hpx installation

export HPX_ROOT={HPX_INSTALL_DIR}
